### Example Formatting Update (INTERNAL – DO NOT OUTPUT)

Replace multi-line example + separate explanation block with single-line format:
Greek — “English” (Citation). Explanation.
Rules:
- One bullet line per example.
- After the closing parenthesis of citation, add a space then the explanation sentence (capital initial, ends with period).
- If no citation: Greek — “English.” Explanation.
- Keep explanation concise (≤ 12 words).
- Role label ("Article:", etc.) dropped unless absolutely needed; write plain text.

Example conversion pattern:

  - Greek NT: "οἱ ἀλώπεκες" — "the foxes" (Matthew 8:20). Refers to a whole class.
  - Greek NT: "ὁ ἐργάτης" — "the worker" (Luke 10:7). Refers to an individual representing a class.
  - Greek NT: "ὁ ἄνθρωπος" — "the man" (John 9:1). Identifies a specific individual.

Validation checklist (internal):
[ ] Each example on one line
[ ] Translation present
[ ] Citation (if source) inside parentheses
[ ] Explanation sentence appended
[ ] No orphan role label lines

Do not output this guidance section.
